Title : William J. Rothwell
Text : {{Orphan|date=August 2016}}

'''Willam J. Rothwell''', (Born on December 17, 1951 in [[Springfield, IL]]) Ph.D., SPHR, CPLP fellow, and Professor of Workforce Education and Development.<ref name="Workforce Education">{{cite web|url=https://www.ed.psu.edu/educ/workforce-ed/Contact/william-j-rothwell |title=PSU LPS |author=Penn State LPS |publisher=Website.education.psu.edu |accessdate=2014-04-22}}</ref> in the Department of Learning and Performance Systems at [[Pennsylvania State University]].  His research includes works in competency modeling, specifically the [[American Society for Training and Development]] Competency Model.<ref name="ASTD">{{cite web|url=https://www.td.org/Publications/Author.aspx?ItemId=DD51CBA40A1442F5A032C801EACCF9D4 |title=William J Rothwell |author=ATD |publisher=Association for Talent Development |accessdate=2015-01-13}}</ref> Rothwell has conducted research in [[Succession planning|Succession Planning]], [[Organization Development]], and [[Instructional Design]].<ref>Rothwell, W.J. (2005), Effective Succession Planning: Ensuring Leadership Continuity and Building Talent from Within, American Management Association, New York, NY</ref><ref>Rothwell, W. J., & Sullivan, R. L. (Eds.). (2005). Practicing organization development: A guide for consultants (Vol. 27). John Wiley & Sons.</ref><ref>Rothwell, W. J., & Kazanas, H. C. (2011). Mastering the instructional design process: A systematic approach. John Wiley & Sons.</ref> As a published author, he is widely held in libraries worldwide.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.worldcat.org/identities/lccn-n86099200/ |title=Rothwell, William J. |publisher=worldcat.org |accessdate=August 29, 2016}}</ref>

==Education==
In 1973 Rothwell obtained a BA in English from [[Illinois State University]], [[Normal, IL]].  He then acquired a MA in English from the University of Illinois, Urbana-Champaign in 1978. The following year he continued his education at Sangamon State University, now known as the [[University of Illinois at Springfield]] and received a M.A.B.A. with a concentration in [[Human Resource Management]].  Simultaneously, Rothwell was enrolled at the [[University of Illinois]], [[Urbana-Champaign]], where he received his doctorate in Education/Employee Training also known as [[Training and development|Training and Development]].

==Teaching career==
In 1993, Rothwell was hired as an Associate Professor of [[Training and development|Human Resource Development]] within Workforce Education and Development at [[Pennsylvania State University]].<ref name="Graduate Faculty"/>  This program is housed within the Learning and Performance Systems department<ref name="Graduate Faculty 2">{{cite web|url=http://www.ed.psu.edu/lps|title=Department of Learning and Performance Systems — Penn State College of Education |author=Penn State University |publisher=Website.education.psu.edu |accessdate=2014-09-11}}</ref> within [[Penn State College of Education|Penn State’s College of Education]].  From 2003 – 2006 he acted as Professor in Charge in the Workforce Education and Development Program, during which they received the #1-ranked graduate program in Workforce Development in the United States.<ref name="Workforce Education 2">{{cite web |url=http://www.ed.psu.edu/lps/workforce-ed/history |title=LPS |author=Penn State University |publisher=Website.education.psu.edu |accessdate=2015-01-13}}</ref> Rothwell was awarded the Graduate Faculty Teaching Award at Pennsylvania State University.<ref name="Faculty Teaching Award">{{cite web|url=http://news.psu.edu/story/211348/2005/03/13/rothwell-receives-graduate-faculty-teaching-award |title=Rothwell Receives Graduate Faculty Teaching award |author=Penn State News |publisher=Website.news.psu.edu |accessdate=2015-01-12}}</ref>

==Research==
===Succession Planning===
Rothwell developed a model on [[Succession planning|Succession Planning]] that is used for training professionals
<ref name="Leadership Advance Online ">{{cite web|url=http://www.regent.edu/acad/global/publications/lao/issue_7/henderson.htm |title=The Value of Succession Planning |author=Henderson |accessdate=2014-09-11}}</ref> and is also included in Canadian Libraries and Librarianship's section on [[Succession planning|Succession Planning]]<ref name="Canadian Libraries and Librarianship ">{{cite web|url= http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/6/7/s7-2600.1-e.html|title=Succession planning: a selective bibliography for librarians|accessdate=2014-09-11}}</ref> From his work on [[succession planning]], Rothwell has broadened his research and practice on the succession topic. One strand of his work examined how succession issues could be examined for knowledge workers<ref name="Graduate Faculty">{{cite web|url=http://www.ed.psu.edu/lps/workforce-ed/contact/william-j-rothwell |title=William Rothwell |author=Penn State University |accessdate=2014-09-11}}</ref>  Rothwell’s work on competencies could also be related to work on [[succession planning]], [[talent management]], and [[training and development]].

==Consultancy/International Travels==
===Consultancy===
Rothwell has served as consultant to business, industry, government, and nonprofit organizations, with clients across 35 nations.  Clients have included [[AccuWeather]], the [[American Red Cross]], the [[American Society for Training and Development]], [[Atotech]], [[CARE]] (the International Relief Agency), the City of Virginia Beach, [[Conoco]], Corning, [[Ford Motor Company]] (Fairlane Center), JLG Industries, [[LandAmerica]], Motorola University U.S., Motorola University China, [[Singapore Airlines]], the [[University of Pittsburgh Medical Center]] (UPMC), the [[U.S. Department of Labor]], and the [[U.S. Postal Service]]<ref name="CV">{{cite web|url=https://www.ed.psu.edu/educ/faculty-cvs/wjr9.pdf |title=Rothwell CV |author=William J. Rothwell |accessdate=2015-01-12}}</ref>

===International Work===
In partnership with [[Peking University]], Rothwell has been involved with Leadership Development studies through [[Training and development|Training and Development]]. The studies focused on four large organizations both locally based or parts of larger global organizations including [[ABB Group]], [[BenQ]], [[Lenovo]] and [[Motorola]].<ref name="Leadereship in China">{{cite web|url=http://illustra.tv/2013/07/leadership-in-china/ |title=Consultancy |author=illustra.tv |publisher=illustra.tv |accessdate=2014-09-11}}</ref> his travels has taken him to Vietnam, where he was able to share his work on local news channel NetViet <ref name="Vietnam">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lQ5vHYEiQ9o |title=Talent, Engagement & Retention |author=NetViet |publisher=Viet Nam Goc Nhim |accessdate=2014-09-18}}</ref>

==Selected works==
Rothwell has authored, co-authored, edited, or co-edited a collection of over 300 books, book chapters, and articles including 80+ books.<ref name="CV"/>

